  "caption": "Figure 3 Arenaviridae . Lifecycle of arenavirids. (1) Virion uptake; (2) virus-cell membrane fusion; (3) uncoating; (4) transcription, translation, and replication; (5) virion assembly; and (6) virion budding. GP, glycoprotein; IGR, intergenic region; L, large protein; NP, nucleoprotein; RNP, ribonucleoprotein; Z, zinc-binding protein. Note that antennaviruses, hartmaniviruses, and innmoviruses do not encode Z, possibly indicating that the lifecycle as depicted here is mammarenavirus-specific.",
